    {
      "texte": "Read a short history of Ancient Greece (recommend Bury's Greece to the Death of Alexander), or just get an an hour of basic outlining on Wikipedia and similar sites. I'd also recommend Toynbee's On Hellenism but you",
      "texte_balise": "Read a short history of Ancient Greece (recommend Bury's Greece to the Death of Alexander), or just get an an hour of basic outlining on Wikipedia and similar sites. I'd also recommend Toynbee's On Hellenism but you",
      "bbox": [
        169.2,
        2598.0,
        1982.1,
        2624.0
      ],
      "confiance": 1.0
    },
    {
      "texte": "probably won't find it and it expects a certain level of British schoolboy knowledge of narrative history. You just want to be able to place the thinkers in some sort of context, especially relative to one another. Ultimately what you",
      "texte_balise": "probably won't find it and it expects a certain level of British schoolboy knowledge of narrative history. You just want to be able to place the thinkers in some sort of context, especially relative to one another. Ultimately what you",
      "bbox": [
        172.4,
        2620.0,
        2017.3,
        2640.0
      ],
      "confiance": 1.0
    },
    {
      "texte": "nost want to understand is that the fifth century is kind of a big deal. Maybe a more in-depth book on Athens in particular (e.g. Kagan's Peloponnesian War), maybe Kagan's Yale course (google it) and its assigned readings",
      "texte_balise": "nost want to understand is that the fifth century is kind of a big deal. Maybe a more in-depth book on Athens in particular (e.g. Kagan's Peloponnesian War), maybe Kagan's Yale course (google it) and its assigned readings",
      "bbox": [
        172.4,
        2639.5,
        1998.1,
        2665.1
      ],
      "confiance": 1.0
    },
    {
      "texte": "maybe look into Teaching Company courses relating to Greece (I recommend Harl). Depends how far you want to go, but knowing the history is vital IMHO.",
      "texte_balise": "maybe look into Teaching Company courses relating to Greece (I recommend Harl). Depends how far you want to go, but knowing the history is vital IMHO.",
      "bbox": [
        166.0,
        2665.0,
        1449.1,
        2687.4
      ],
      "confiance": 1.0
    },
    {
      "texte": "Suffer through Homer and Hesiod if you're a completionist. I think Fitzgerald is the best Homer, but use this:",
      "texte_balise": "Suffer through Homer and Hesiod if you're a completionist. I think Fitzgerald is the best Homer, but use this:",
      "bbox": [
