      "confiance": 1.0
    },
    {
      "texte": "For fifth century history, start with Herodotus, then Thucydides (get Landmark versions of both), then Xenophon (no Landmark yet, get a well-annotated one with maps though). Again look at Kagan's Yale course (for which you",
      "texte_balise": "For fifth century history, start with Herodotus, then Thucydides (get Landmark versions of both), then Xenophon (no Landmark yet, get a well-annotated one with maps though). Again look at Kagan's Yale course (for which you",
      "bbox": [
